  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `1.5.0`\nOS & Version: Linux\n#### Expected behaviour\n\nShould provide a way to know the last instruction error'ed\n#### Actual behaviour\n\nDoes not report error\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n\nTrace for 0x0b157cbbcca6079664e1f61e5f5e33241999c1cc1a7dbc1adad347b904c0fb65 gives no error, while it actually failed (confirmed by getBalance and checking in etherscan & ether.camp)\n\nAFAICT this is because in vm.go, the captureState call is made before the opcode is evaluated, so if the last instruction runs out of gas for instance, that error is never logged (or maybe some bug with the cost evaluation for RETURN?)\n",
