    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Problem is \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/vm/interpreter.go#L219\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/vm/interpreter.go#L223\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/vm/interpreter.go#L257\r\n\r\n^ the `err` is redeclared `:=`, and is thus not visible to `CaptureFault` which is deferred here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/vm/interpreter.go#L197\r\n\r\nThe only place that is correct is here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/core/vm/interpreter.go#L243 \r\n\r\nSo the fix should be to use `=` instead of `:=`. \r\n",
